cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the assignment of transmission powers in wireless ad hoc networks. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of minimum spanning trees and traveling salesman tours in the analysis of the power assignment problem. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of transmit power to maximize the life-time of the network. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with the connectivity of the communication graph in wireless ad hoc networks. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the coordination of wireless devices in a network.
